stylometry: When we set the price of a product/service we have to take into consideration the demand for the product.  The unit price of the product has to be low if the demand is low, and the higher the demand for the product the higher the price will be because people will buy it anyways.  If the product is difficult to come by because of shortages, the demand will be higher, so the price will be higher.  The best example of this is gasoline.  When the BP oil spill happened, the price of oil was higher because they had lost so much of it and needed to make that money back and gasoline is a necessity for most people so they had no choice but to pay the higher price.
